{{Infobox government agency | agency_name = Department of Energy | type = department | nativename = {{collapsible list |titlestyle = background:transparent;text-align:left;padding-left:2.5em;font-size:85%;<!--size of [show]/[hide] link--> |liststyle = text-align:center;white-space:nowrap; | {{small|{{nobold|''10 other official names:''}}}} | {{native name|af|{{small|Departement van Energie}}|fontsize=68%}} | {{native name|nr|{{small|umNyango wezaMandla}}|fontsize=68%}} | {{native name|xh|{{small|iSebe leMandla}}|fontsize=68%}} | {{native name|zu|{{small|uMnyango wezaMandla}}|fontsize=68%}} | {{native name|ss|{{small|Litiko leTemandla}}|fontsize=68%}} | {{native name|nso|{{small|Kgoro ya Enetši}}|fontsize=68%}} | {{native name|st|{{small|Lefapha la Eneji}}|fontsize=68%}} | {{native name|tn|{{small|Lefapha la Maatla}}|fontsize=68%}} | {{native name|ts|{{small|Ndzawulo ya Eneji}}|fontsize=68%}} | {{native name|ve|{{small|Muhasho wa Fulufulu}}|fontsize=68%}} }} | nativename_a = | nativename_r = | logo = | logo_width = | logo_caption = | seal = | seal_width = | seal_caption = | picture = | picture_width = | picture_caption = | formed = {{Start date|2009|07|07|df=y}} | preceding1 = [[Department of Minerals and Energy (South Africa)|Department of Minerals and Energy]] | dissolved = | superseding = | jurisdiction = [[Government of South Africa]] | headquarters = 192 Visagie Street, [[Pretoria]] | coordinates = {{coord|-25.752|28.188|type:landmark_region:ZA|display=inline}} | employees = 622 <small>(2016/17)</small> | budget = [[South African rand|R]]7,45 million <small>(2016/17)</small> | minister1_name = [[Jeff Radebe]] | minister1_pfo = [[Minister of Energy (South Africa)|Minister of Energy]] | deputyminister1_name = Ms Thembisile Majola | deputyminister1_pfo = Deputy Minister of Energy | chief1_name = Mr. Thabane Zulu | chief1_position = Director-General: Energy | chief2_name = | chief2_position = | chief3_name = | chief3_position = | chief4_name = | chief4_position = | chief5_name = | chief5_position = | agency_type = Department | chief6_name = | chief6_position = | chief7_name = | chief7_position = | chief8_name = | chief8_position = | chief9_name = | chief9_position = | parent_department = | parent_agency = | child1_agency = [[National Energy Regulator of South Africa]] | child2_agency = [[National Nuclear Regulator]] | child3_agency = [[Central Energy Fund]] | child4_agency = [[South African Nuclear Energy Corporation]] | child5_agency = [[Electricity Distribution Industry Holdings]]<!-- (etc.) --> | keydocument1 = National Energy Act, 2008 | website = {{URL|www.energy.gov.za}} | footnotes = | map = | map_width = | map_caption = }} The '''Department of Energy''' is the [[government department|department]] of the [[South African government]] responsible for [[energy policy]]. It was established in 2009 when the former [[Department of Minerals and Energy (South Africa)|Department of Minerals and Energy]] was divided into the Department of Energy and the [[Department of Mineral Resources]].
From 2012 to 2014, the [[Minister of Energy (South Africa)|Minister of Energy]] was Ben Martins and his deputy was [[Barbara Thompson (South African politician)|Barbara Thompson]]. [[Tina Joemat-Pettersson]] MP has been the Minister of Energy since 25 May 2014 . She was previously the [[Minister of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries (South Africa)|Minister of Agriculture, Forestry, and Fisheries]] from 2009-2014.<ref name="za2009-05-10">{{Cite web |title=Statement by President Jacob Zuma on the appointment of the new Cabinet |url=http://www.info.gov.za/events/2009/new_cabinet.htm |publisher=South African Government Information |date=2009-05-10 |accessdate=2009-05-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090513025048/http://www.info.gov.za/events/2009/new_cabinet.htm |archivedate=2009-05-13 |df= }}</ref> After Tine Joemat-Petterson was asked to leave, Mmamoloko Kubayi was appointed. This only lasted 7 months before the next reshuffle and the appointment of [[David Mahlobo]]. His appointment was potentially linked to securing the planned Russian nuclear deal - a country he had just visited as Minister of State Security.[http://www.fin24.com/Economy/david-mahlobo-the-nuclear-deals-new-best-friend-20171017 link]
President [[Cyril Ramaphosa]] appointed [[Jeff Radebe]] as Minister as part of his cabinet reshuffle on 26 January 2018.
In the 2016/2017 budget the department had a budget of [[South African rand|R]]7,545 million and a staff complement of 622 civil servants.<ref>{{cite book |title=Estimates of National Expenditure 2016 |publisher=National Treasury |location=Pretoria |isbn=978-0-621-44244-1 |date=24 February 2016 |chapter=Vote 26: Energy |url=http://www.treasury.gov.za/documents/national%20budget/2016/enebooklets/default.aspx |chapterurl=http://www.treasury.gov.za/documents/national%20budget/2016/enebooklets/Vote%2026%20Energy.pdf |accessdate=6 January 2012}}</ref>
In August 2018, the Department of Energy released a draft of South Africa's updated Integrated Resource Plan (IRP), the plan which seeks to meet the country's energy consumption demands, for public comment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://africaoilandpower.com/2018/08/28/south-african-government-releases-integrated-resource-plan-draft/|title=South African government releases Integrated Resource Plan draft|publisher=''Africa Oil and Power''|accessdate=10 September 2018}}</ref> The current plan dropped proposals for expansion of the number of nuclear plants in the country, focusing instead on expanding the production of renewable energy and creating two new coal power plants.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/article/2018-08-29-draft-energy-irp-welcomed-but-some-doubts-remain/|title=Draft energy IRP welcomed, but some doubts remain|publisher=''Daily Maverick''|author=Melanie Gosling|accessdate=10 September 2018}}</ref>
