The '''Shapley attractor''' is an attractor located about the [[Shapley Supercluster]].<ref>{{cite journal |title=The dipole repeller |author=Yehuda Hoffman |author2=Daniel Pomarède |author3=R. Brent Tully |author4=Hélène M. Courtois|authorlink4=Hélène Courtois|journal=Nature Astronomy |date=January 30, 2017 |volume=1 |page=36 | doi=10.1038/s41550-016-0036|arxiv = 1702.02483 |bibcode = 2017NatAs...1E..36H }}</ref>

It is opposed to the [[Dipole Repeller]], in the [[CMB Dipole]] of local galactic flow. It is thought to be the composite contributions of the [[Shapley Concentration]] and the [[Great Attractor]].

